headers.Content-Type: Indicates the media type of the request body
headers.Accept: Specifies the media types the client is willing to accept
headers.User-Agent: Provides information about the client application
headers.Location: Specifies the URL to redirect the recipient to
headers.ETag: A unique identifier for a specific version of a resource
headers.Last-Modified: Indicates the date and time at which the origin server believes the resource was last modified
headers.Content-Encoding: Indicates the compression method used on the message body
headers.Content-Language: Describes the natural language(s) of the intended audience for the content
headers.Content-Length: Indicates the size of the response body
headers.Transfer-Encoding: Specifies the form of encoding used to safely transfer the resource to the user
headers.Content-Disposition: Indicates if the content is expected to be displayed inline in the browser or as an attachment to be downloaded
headers.Host: Specifies the domain name of the server (for virtual hosting)
headers.Referer: Indicates the source URL of the current request
headers.Origin: Indicates the origin of the request
headers.Cookie: Sends cookies from the client to the server
